Automatic translation

Automatic translation

The good

  • Quick and easy to use.

  • Context and idioms included.

  • Convey the sense of the source.

Automatic translation

The bad

  • Complex source becomes garbage.

  • Occasionally missing words like "not".

  • Online tools present a security risk.

Automatic translation

Best uses

  • Bulk translation that you will then check and rewrite.

  • Getting the sense of a text for your own reference.

  • Testing whether you’re writing simple, clear English.
